cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper is about comparing clustering algorithms for pattern recognition tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also discusses the sensitivity of clustering methods to their parameters configuration, which is related to optimization and search algorithms, making cs.SI (Search and Optimization) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper uses artificial datasets with tunable properties, which is a common approach in computer vision, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
